&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Getting It Right for Every Child&lt;/strong&gt; (GIRFEC) is the national approach to improving the wellbeing of all children and young people in Scotland through policy and the delivery of services at both national and local level.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GIRFEC&lt;/strong&gt; is important for everyone who works with children and young people as well as many people who work with adults who look after children.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;This means it is an approach not simply for those working in services focusing directly on children, but also for those in services with an indirect impact on children. Services that support the wider family or community, or focused on adults can still have a powerful role in supporting children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;HTMLContentText&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Getting It Right for Every Child &lt;/strong&gt;approach&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;This about how you and practitioners across all services for children and adults meet the needs of children and young people, working together to ensure they have the best possible start and reach their full potential.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;div.SP1_AdvancedBlue { 
	background: #D2E3EA;
	border-radius: 10px 10px 10px 10px;
    box-shadow: 3px 3px 1px #888888;
    color: #163880;
    padding: 10px 15px 10px 15px;
    margin: 10px 0px 10px 0px;
}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_Content&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Views of Children and Young People&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The GIRFEC approach ensures that anyone providing support puts the child or young person and their family at the centre.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;This means that it is important that the child or young person and family have their views listened to and are involved fully in decisions that affect them.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;div.SP1_AdvancedBlue { 
	background: #D2E3EA;
	border-radius: 10px 10px 10px 10px;
