    padding: 10px 15px 10px 15px;
    margin: 10px 0px 10px 0px;
}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_Content&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_ImageWithDText&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;National Practice Model&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The National Practice Model is an evidence based tool used by practitioners to support early intervention and early identification of concerns. This is used to review the child&amp;#39;s wellbeing based on the wellbeing indicators.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;The National Practice Model has 3 main steps which we will explore on the next 5 pages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div style=&quot;clear: both;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;div.SP1_AdvancedBlue { 
	background: #D2E3EA;
	border-radius: 10px 10px 10px 10px;
    box-shadow: 3px 3px 1px #888888;
    color: #163880;
    padding: 10px 15px 10px 15px;
    margin: 10px 0px 10px 0px;
}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_Content&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Step 1: Observing using the Wellbeing Wheel&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Using the Wellbeing Wheel shown in the National Practice Model, the wellbeing indicators are used to identify needs or potential concerns.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The 8 indicators are areas in which children and young people need to progress in order to do well now and in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;script src=&quot;javascript/htmlinteraction141.js&quot; type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;script src=&quot;javascript/htmlinteraction142.js&quot; type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

