&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Section 3: Information Sharing and Managing Concerns&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;All practitioners working with children and young people must play their part in supporting the wellbeing of children and young people to ensure they are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Safe&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Healthy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Achieving&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Nurtured&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Active&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Respected&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Responsible&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Included&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;HTMLContentText&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Effective early intervention necessitates appropriate and proportionate information sharing in a timely manner as well as consideration of confidentiality and consent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;For the purposes of processing information in relation to child protection matters, &lt;strong&gt;General Data Protection Regulations &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;strong&gt;GDPR) will have no impact on practitioners&amp;#39; ability to share proportionate and relevant information to appropriate authorities in exactly the same circumstances as they now do. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Currently, child protection matters are considered to be up at the significant harm bar and that equates to processing being necessary to protect the vital interests of the child and the reliance on consent may be prejudicial to that purpose. The same lawful purpose is provided for in the GDPR for both personal and sensitive personal information so nothing will change in that regard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;div.SP1_AdvancedBlue { 
	background: #D2E3EA;
	border-radius: 10px 10px 10px 10px;
    box-shadow: 3px 3px 1px #888888;
    color: #163880;
    padding: 10px 15px 10px 15px;
    margin: 10px 0px 10px 0px;
}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_Content&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_ImageWithDText&quot; style=&quot;float: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;lP_DText&quot; id=&quot;lP_imgD_1&quot; style=&quot;width: 474px; display: none;&quot;&gt;9 children lying down in height order&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Chronology&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chronologies are a valuable tool for the assessment and analysis of needs and risks and can highlight the need to protect from harm&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A chronology requires to be well maintained to be of most value to the assessment process&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Information should be recorded in sequential order to create a timeline that highlights patterns of events, behaviour or lifestyle trends, that are significant for a child or family&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Information within chronologies should be a succinct and systematic way of organising information to help it make sense to the reader&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chronologies may also highlight gaps in information that require further clarification, exploration and assessment moving forward. (Care Inspectorate. 2017)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;HTMLContentText&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;In addition to single agency chronologies, multi-agency chronologies require to be used at the point when risk(s) to a child needs to be assessed from a multi-agency perspective:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Examples of these points include, but are not exclusive to, Child Protection Case Conferences or Children&amp;#39;s Hearings&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is the role of the Lead Professional to amalgamate single agency chronologies into a multi-agency chronology (Pan Lothian Guidance on Chronologies. 2020)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Multi-agency chronologies allow an informed assessment to be made for children at risk&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This assessment is made through all agencies involved with the child, or significant adults in a child life, sharing &lt;strong&gt;only relevant and proportionate information &lt;/strong&gt;(Inter Agency Child Protection Procedures Edinburgh and Lothian. 2015)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;div.SP1_AdvancedBlue { 
	background: #D2E3EA;
	border-radius: 10px 10px 10px 10px;
