&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;lP_Content&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Pan-Lothian Chronology (cont&amp;#39;d)&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;When appropriate, chronologies are a tool that can be used with families. For example, gaps in chronologies can be explored with families and may indicate a time when a child&amp;#39;s needs were successfully being met. During these periods, circumstances can be explored to identify strengths within a child and family&amp;#39;s life. These strengths can then be built upon whilst working in partnership with families.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Further guidance on the use of Chronologies can be found via the following links:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot;  href=&quot;https://www.gov.scot/publications/national-risk-framework-support-assessment-children-young-people/&quot; &gt;Care Inspectorate - A Practice Guide to Chronologies&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

